Sentencas: Composite electrodes of Cu0.16Ni0.27Zn0.37Ce0.16Gd0.04 (CNZGC) oxides have been successfully synthesized by solid state reaction method as anode material for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LTSOFC).
Titulo: Study of CuNiZnGdCe-Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: These electrodes are characterized by XRD followed by sintering at various time periods and temperatures.
Titulo: Study of CuNiZnGdCe-Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Particle size of optimized composition was calculated 40-85 nm and sintered at 800 degrees C for 4 hours.
Titulo: Study of CuNiZnGdCe-Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity of 4.14 S/cm was obtained at a temperature of 550 degrees C by the 4-prob DC method.
Titulo: Study of CuNiZnGdCe-Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The activation energy was calculated 4 x 10(-2) eV at 550 degrees C. Hydrogen was used as fuel and air as oxidant at anode and cathode sides respectively.
Titulo: Study of CuNiZnGdCe-Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: I-V/I-P curves were obtained in the temperature range of 400-550 degrees C.
Titulo: Study of CuNiZnGdCe-Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The maximum power density was achieved for 570 mW/cm(2) at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Study of CuNiZnGdCe-Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFC
